Package com.sanyavertolet.interview.parser

Interface ExpressionParser

All Known Implementing Classes:
ShuntingYardParser
public interface ExpressionParser
An interface for parsing expressions into Expression objects. The ExpressionParser interface defines the method for converting a string representation of an expression into a structured Expression that can be evaluated or further processed.

    parse(String expression)

  • Method Details

    • parse

      Expression parse(String expression) throws ExpressionParsingException
      Parses the given expression string and converts it into an Expression object. The method processes the input string to build a structured representation of the expression, which can be evaluated or manipulated programmatically.
      Parameters:
      expression - the string representation of the expression to be parsed.
      Returns:
      an Expression object representing the parsed expression.
      Throws:
      ExpressionParsingException - if an error occurs during parsing, such as invalid syntax or unrecognized tokens.
